# Template-net10 — Cursor rules (legacy .cursorrules)

This repository is a fully documented .NET 10 starter kit. The documentation is the source of truth.
Read it before writing code, and keep it up to date.

Read first (required, in order):
1. AGENTS.md — primary operating guide (architecture, conventions, golden rules, recipes). Authoritative.
2. docs/ARCHITECTURE.md — long-form architecture reference.
3. docs-site/content/** — per-feature usage docs (auth, caching, storage, encryption, excel, pdf,
   realtime/websockets, idempotency, helpers, docker, …).

Non-negotiable rules:
- Follow every convention and Golden rule in AGENTS.md. Search the docs before inventing a pattern.
- Match existing code: Clean Architecture + CQRS + MediatR; feature-organized folders; namespace == folder path.
- When you add or change a feature, update the docs: docs-site/content/** (+ docs-site/src/lib/navigation.ts),
  and AGENTS.md / docs/ARCHITECTURE.md if conventions change.
- A task is done only when `dotnet build Template-net10.slnx` is green and `dotnet test` passes.
- Do not introduce forbidden patterns: Repository pattern, business logic in handlers/controllers,
  hardcoded user-facing strings, multi-tenancy, or hand-authored EF migrations.

Treat AGENTS.md as the canonical rule set; this file only points you to it.
